The paper deals with motion planning for robots, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). The use of knowledge-based reasoning is a key aspect of the proposed approach, which suggests that it could also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a semantic abstract knowledge described in terms of an ontology, which suggests that it could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). The approach involves the use of a low-level geometric reasoning process, which suggests that it could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
